<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#d8abada8a8b7aaac98bab1b6b9aaa1bdbcbfbdf6b1b7"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="c0b3b5b0b0afb2b480a2a9aea1b2b9a5a4a7a5eea9af">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#d8abada8a8b7aaac98bab1b6b9aaa1bdbcbfbdf6b1b7"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="c0b3b5b0b0afb2b480a2a9aea1b2b9a5a4a7a5eea9af">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#b5c6c0c5c5dac7c1f5d7dcdbd4c7ccd0d1d2d09bdcda"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="34474144445b464074565d5a55464d515053511a5d5b">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#b5c6c0c5c5dac7c1f5d7dcdbd4c7ccd0d1d2d09bdcda"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="34474144445b464074565d5a55464d515053511a5d5b">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>
</div>

        var elNewLink = document.getElementById('redirect-link-new');
        var redirectUrl = '';
                        if (elNewLink.dataset.hostname === window.location.hostname) {
            redirectUrl = elNewLink.href;
            var ipMatch = window.location.pathname.match(/\/([.0-9]+)$/);
            var ip = ipMatch && typeof ipMatch[1] !== 'undefined' ? '/' + ipMatch[1] : '';
            redirectUrl = redirectUrl.replace('/0.0.0.0', ip);
            elNewLink.style.display = 'inline';
            elNewLink.href = redirectUrl;
            document.getElementById('redirect-link-old').style.display = 'none';
        } else {
            redirectUrl = document.getElementById('redirect-link-old').href;
        }

        window.location.href = redirectUrl;
    </script>
</body>

            redirectUrl = document.getElementById('redirect-link-old').href;
        }

        window.location.href = redirectUrl;
    </script>
</body>
</html>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#4a393f3a3a25383e0a2823242b38332f2e2d2f642325"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="4a393f3a3a25383e0a2823242b38332f2e2d2f642325">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#4a393f3a3a25383e0a2823242b38332f2e2d2f642325"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="4a393f3a3a25383e0a2823242b38332f2e2d2f642325">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>
</div>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#f4878184849b8680b4969d9a95868d91909391da9d9b"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="a6d5d3d6d6c9d4d2e6c4cfc8c7d4dfc3c2c1c388cfc9">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#f4878184849b8680b4969d9a95868d91909391da9d9b"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="a6d5d3d6d6c9d4d2e6c4cfc8c7d4dfc3c2c1c388cfc9">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#661513161609141226040f0807141f03020103480f09"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="ed9e989d9d829f99ad8f84838c9f9488898a88c38482">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#661513161609141226040f0807141f03020103480f09"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="ed9e989d9d829f99ad8f84838c9f9488898a88c38482">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>
</div>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#21525451514e53556143484f405358444546440f484e"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="abd8dedbdbc4d9dfebc9c2c5cad9d2cecfccce85c2c4">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>

</article>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#21525451514e53556143484f405358444546440f484e"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="abd8dedbdbc4d9dfebc9c2c5cad9d2cecfccce85c2c4">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>

</article>
</div>
</div>
</main>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#c4b7b1b4b4abb6b084a6adaaa5b6bda1a0a3a1eaadab"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="087b7d7878677a7c486a6166697a716d6c6f6d266167">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>

</article>
</div>
</div>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#c4b7b1b4b4abb6b084a6adaaa5b6bda1a0a3a1eaadab"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="087b7d7878677a7c486a6166697a716d6c6f6d266167">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>

</article>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#5e2d2b2e2e312c2a1e3c37303f2c273b3a393b703731"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="8efdfbfefee1fcfaceece7e0effcf7ebeae9eba0e7e1">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#5e2d2b2e2e312c2a1e3c37303f2c273b3a393b703731"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="8efdfbfefee1fcfaceece7e0effcf7ebeae9eba0e7e1">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>

<div class="md-content" data-md-component="content">
<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#e89b9d9898879a9ca88a8186899a918d8c8f8dc68187"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="c0b3b5b0b0afb2b480a2a9aea1b2b9a5a4a7a5eea9af">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>

<article class="md-content__inner md-typeset">
<h1 id="scanning-engine-v2-blocking">Scanning Engine v2 - Blocking<a class="headerlink" href="#scanning-engine-v2-blocking" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h1>
<h2 id="introduction">Introduction<a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>Our scanning engine is comprised of a cluster coordinator called 'Krang' and thousands of hosts called 'Minions' that survey the entire publicly-addressable Internet on a regular basis. Due to these surveys and other research, you may have received traffic originating from our Minions. If you would prefer not to receive traffic from us in future, you have two options: blocking on our side or blocking on your side.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-our-side">Blocking on Our Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-our-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We recommend this method because it is the most reliable. To have your IP addresses or network ranges added to our blocklist, please email us at <a href="/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection#e89b9d9898879a9ca88a8186899a918d8c8f8dc68187"><span class="__cf_email__" data-cfemail="c0b3b5b0b0afb2b480a2a9aea1b2b9a5a4a7a5eea9af">[email&#160;protected]</span></a>. Please include the following information:</p>
<ol>
<li>Your name and the organization you represent, if any</li>
<li>The IP addresses or network ranges you'd like us to block on our side</li>
<li>The date, time, and addresses, if any, that contacted your hosts</li>
</ol>
<p>This information will help us double-check that the scanning engine was the source of the traffic you received, ensure that there are no other sources of traffic coming from us, and get back to you if we have additional questions.</p>
<h2 id="blocking-on-your-side">Blocking on Your Side<a class="headerlink" href="#blocking-on-your-side" title="Permanent link">&para;</a></h2>
<p>We do not recommend this method because the hosts from which our scans originate are ephemeral and not associated with their IP addresses over the long-term. We publish an up-to-the-moment list of the addresses currently associated with our Minions <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/krang/v1/minions">here</a>. Its format is as follows:</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
  &quot;scanners&quot;: [
    &quot;ipv4-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv4-address-N&quot;,
    &quot;ipv6-address-1&quot;,
    ...
    &quot;ipv6-address-M&quot;
  ]
}
</code></pre>
<p>The list of Minion addresses for v1 of our scanning engine are available <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions">here (IPv4)</a> and <a href="https://api.binaryedge.io/v1/minions-ipv6">here (IPv6)</a>. Please note that all of these endpoints are rate-limited, meaning if you request them too often you will receive <code>HTTP 429 Too Many Requests</code> responses.</p>
</article>
</div>

      <section id="about">
        <h1 class="header">Green Box Code</h1>
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <a href="https://unsplash.com/@alexazabache" target="_blank">
          <img src='images/resized/alex-azabache-QM61C6shPZY-unsplash.jpg' class="med_image"
            alt="Woman in an van style RV looking out at mountains, thought the back doors">
        </a>
        <p>Welcome to Green Box Code, the pioneering open-source software solutions company committed to delivering
          powerful solutions for our SMB<sup><a href="#fn-1">1</a></sup> customers. We are dedicated to empowering
          businesses by harnessing advanced
          Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) based technology.</p>

        <p>At Green Box Code, our mission is to provide SMB customers with easy access to our cutting-edge software and
          services. Our open-source<sup><a href="#fn-2">2</a></sup> platform is designed to streamline the process of
          building, deploying, and managing
          customized solutions. With comprehensive documentation, tutorials, and support, we ensure our customers can
          fully leverage the potential of their GNSS solutions.</p>

        <p>We don't stop there. We are constantly pushing the boundaries of innovation and are proud to spearhead the
          development of a groundbreaking mobile network solution. This solution is tailored specifically for content
          creators, road warriors, and full time RVers, revolutionizing their connectivity and productivity on the go.
        </p>
        <div>
          <p class="footnote" id="fn-1">1. Small and Medium-Sized Business</a></p>
          <p class="footnote" id="fn-2">2. Open-source software is software with source code that anyone can inspect,
            modify, and enhance.</a></p>
        </div><!--Footnotes-->
      </section>
      <section id="services">
        <h1>Services</h1>
        <hr>
        <h2>Mobile / Rv</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h3>Mobile Asset Tracking</h3>
            <a href="https://unsplash.com/@dhueske"><img class="med_image"
                src="images/resized/darla-hueske-g7HW8daVsDA-unsplash.jpg"
                alt="Farm equipment with GPS navigation equipment"></a>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Live tracking with inertial navigation in urban canyons.</li>
            <li>Geo-fencing with push notifications to supervisors.</li>
            <li>Speed limit violations</li>
            <li>Use captured data for event analysis, and coaching opportunities.</li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            <h3>Asset Mapping</h3>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Stationary asset location management with bluetooth tags.</li>
            <li>Inventory flow analysis with bluetooth tags, and check points.</li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            <h3>Yard & Warehouse Analysis</h3>

          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Pedestrian and vehicle flow analysis.</li>
            <li>Identify potential hazard areas using positional heatmaps.</li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            <h3>AI Video Parking Lot Management</h3>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Open stall counts</li>
            <li>Automatic monitoring of time limited zones</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
        <h2>Coding</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h3>Database</h3>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>GNSS disciplined timestamps</li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            <h3>Geoinformatics</h3>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h3>Location Data Conversions</h3>
          </li>
          <ul>
            <li>UTM <--> Lat & lon</li>
            <li>Maidenhead <--> Lat & Lon</li>
          </ul>
          <li>
            <h3>Scripting</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Server & Database backups</li>
              <li>Automated Updating</li>
              <li>Event Analysis and push notifications</li>
              <li>Logging Analysis and Dashboards</li>
            </ul>
        </ul>
      </section>

            redirectUrl = elNewLink.href;
            var ipMatch = window.location.pathname.match(/\/([.0-9]+)$/);

<article id="post-4" class="post-4 page type-page status-publish hentry wpautop">
		<div class="entry-content clearfix">
		<h1>Purpose</h1>
<p>The Lindsay Memorial Foundation is a small, private, not-for-profit charitable foundation created under Federal Charter in 1972, and dedicated to the <b>older adult</b> population.¬†No funds are solicited. Disbursement funding comes from income earned on investments.</p>
<h1>Our Mission</h1>
<p>To operate exclusively as a charitable organization for the sole purposes of providing funding to organizations/programs that focus on relieving poverty, promoting health, lessening isolation and loneliness, advancing education,¬†and improving the quality of life of¬†<b>older adults</b>. To furnish funds for the care, treatment and support of any such persons, to any charitable organization that is a qualified donee as described in subsection 149.1 (1) of the Income Tax Act (Canada).</p>
<h1>About Us</h1>
<p>The Lindsay Memorial Foundation Board of Directors consists of 5-15 members who reflect a variety of backgrounds and expertise (healthcare, community service, social work, finance, law, and business), and have an interest in promoting the well-being of <b>older adults</b> in the community. The board meets approximately 6 times a year.</p>
<h2>Executive</h2>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Jan-Lariviere.jpg" alt="Jan Lariviere: President" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>PRESIDENT ‚Äì <strong>Jan Lariviere</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional with experience in family nursing, education, literacy, and project management.</p>
</div>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Jean-McLaughlin.jpg" alt="Jean McLaughlin" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>VICE-PRESIDENT ‚Äì <strong>Jean McLaughlin</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional with experience in pediatric rehabilitation and multidisciplinary team coordination.</p>
</div>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Jennifer-Hawke.jpg" alt="Jennifer Hawke" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>TREASURER ‚Äì <strong>Jennifer Hawke</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional with experience in paediatrics and geriatrics.</p>
</div>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Janet-Cholette.jpg" alt="Janet Grassby Cholette" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>SECRETARY ‚Äì <strong>Janet Grassby Cholette</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional. Worked with children with physical challenges. Volunteer facilitator: ‚ÄúGood Grief Workshops‚Äù for Children and Adolescents.</p>
</div>
<h1>What We Fund</h1>
<p>The Lindsay Memorial Foundation provides financial support to registered community organizations and/or institutions whose mission is to improve the quality of life of the <b>older adult</b> population in Montreal and surrounding areas.<b>¬†</b></p>
<p><b>(Although there may be exceptions, LMF defines ‚Äòolder adults‚Äô as those 65 and over).¬†</b></p>
<p>We prioritize projects/programs that focus on:</p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1">Food supply</li>
<li aria-level="1">Clothing &amp; Shelter</li>
<li aria-level="1">Transportation</li>
<li aria-level="1">Health promotion ( physical, cognitive, mental health, psychosocial needs)</li>
<li aria-level="1">Social Isolation &amp; Loneliness</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>¬†Please see the <a href="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Articles-of-Continuance-Prorogation-LMF.pdf">Articles of Continuance</a> for further details.</strong></p>
<p><b>FUNDS ARE DISBURSED ONCE A YEAR IN NOVEMBER.¬† ALL APPLICATIONS MUST BE <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">SUBMITTED BY SEPTEMBER 15th</span> in order to be considered for grant funding.¬†</b></p>
<p>Applications are reviewed by a Board of Directors who follows pre-established criteria and policies for disbursement. <b>Grants are typically in the $3,000-$25,000 range</b>. Funding is dependent on the nature of the request, our total disbursement budget for the year, and the number of applications received. The majority of grants are given for a period of one year, although some may be considered for sustainable funding, up to 3 years. <b>First-time applicants may not request sustainable funding.</b></p>
<h1>Documents Required</h1>
<ol>
<li>Grant Application: <b>Only the on-line Application Form will be accepted.¬†</b><b>If this is not possible, please contact us by e-mail for an alternative at </b><a href="mailto:lindsaymemorialfoundation@gmail.com"><b>lindsaymemorialfoundation@gmail.com</b></a><b>¬†¬†</b></li>
<li>Most recent Annual Report</li>
<li>Most recent Financial Report.</li>
<li>Please submit all information with the Grant Application.¬†It is not necessary to add a cover letter.¬†Any supplemental information can be included in the section ‚ÄúOther Comments‚Äù.</li>
</ol>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->

<article id="post-4" class="post-4 page type-page status-publish hentry wpautop">
		<div class="entry-content clearfix">
		<h1>Purpose</h1>
<p>The Lindsay Memorial Foundation is a small, private, not-for-profit charitable foundation created under Federal Charter in 1972, and dedicated to the <b>older adult</b> population.¬†No funds are solicited. Disbursement funding comes from income earned on investments.</p>
<h1>Our Mission</h1>
<p>To operate exclusively as a charitable organization for the sole purposes of providing funding to organizations/programs that focus on relieving poverty, promoting health, lessening isolation and loneliness, advancing education,¬†and improving the quality of life of¬†<b>older adults</b>. To furnish funds for the care, treatment and support of any such persons, to any charitable organization that is a qualified donee as described in subsection 149.1 (1) of the Income Tax Act (Canada).</p>
<h1>About Us</h1>
<p>The Lindsay Memorial Foundation Board of Directors consists of 5-15 members who reflect a variety of backgrounds and expertise (healthcare, community service, social work, finance, law, and business), and have an interest in promoting the well-being of <b>older adults</b> in the community. The board meets approximately 6 times a year.</p>
<h2>Executive</h2>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Jan-Lariviere.jpg" alt="Jan Lariviere: President" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>PRESIDENT ‚Äì <strong>Jan Lariviere</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional with experience in family nursing, education, literacy, and project management.</p>
</div>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Jean-McLaughlin.jpg" alt="Jean McLaughlin" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>VICE-PRESIDENT ‚Äì <strong>Jean McLaughlin</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional with experience in pediatric rehabilitation and multidisciplinary team coordination.</p>
</div>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Jennifer-Hawke.jpg" alt="Jennifer Hawke" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>TREASURER ‚Äì <strong>Jennifer Hawke</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional with experience in paediatrics and geriatrics.</p>
</div>
<div id="staff">
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Janet-Cholette.jpg" alt="Janet Grassby Cholette" width="140" height="175" /></p>
<p>SECRETARY ‚Äì <strong>Janet Grassby Cholette</strong><br />
Retired nursing professional. Worked with children with physical challenges. Volunteer facilitator: ‚ÄúGood Grief Workshops‚Äù for Children and Adolescents.</p>
</div>
<h1>What We Fund</h1>
<p>The Lindsay Memorial Foundation provides financial support to registered community organizations and/or institutions whose mission is to improve the quality of life of the <b>older adult</b> population in Montreal and surrounding areas.<b>¬†</b></p>
<p><b>(Although there may be exceptions, LMF defines ‚Äòolder adults‚Äô as those 65 and over).¬†</b></p>
<p>We prioritize projects/programs that focus on:</p>
<ul>
<li aria-level="1">Food supply</li>
<li aria-level="1">Clothing &amp; Shelter</li>
<li aria-level="1">Transportation</li>
<li aria-level="1">Health promotion ( physical, cognitive, mental health, psychosocial needs)</li>
<li aria-level="1">Social Isolation &amp; Loneliness</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>¬†Please see the <a href="http://vvd6f6p8729.c.updraftclone.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/Articles-of-Continuance-Prorogation-LMF.pdf">Articles of Continuance</a> for further details.</strong></p>
<p><b>FUNDS ARE DISBURSED ONCE A YEAR IN NOVEMBER.¬† ALL APPLICATIONS MUST BE <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">SUBMITTED BY SEPTEMBER 15th</span> in order to be considered for grant funding.¬†</b></p>
<p>Applications are reviewed by a Board of Directors who follows pre-established criteria and policies for disbursement. <b>Grants are typically in the $3,000-$25,000 range</b>. Funding is dependent on the nature of the request, our total disbursement budget for the year, and the number of applications received. The majority of grants are given for a period of one year, although some may be considered for sustainable funding, up to 3 years. <b>First-time applicants may not request sustainable funding.</b></p>
<h1>Documents Required</h1>
<ol>
<li>Grant Application: <b>Only the on-line Application Form will be accepted.¬†</b><b>If this is not possible, please contact us by e-mail for an alternative at </b><a href="mailto:lindsaymemorialfoundation@gmail.com"><b>lindsaymemorialfoundation@gmail.com</b></a><b>¬†¬†</b></li>
<li>Most recent Annual Report</li>
<li>Most recent Financial Report.</li>
<li>Please submit all information with the Grant Application.¬†It is not necessary to add a cover letter.¬†Any supplemental information can be included in the section ‚ÄúOther Comments‚Äù.</li>
</ol>
			</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
	</article><!-- #post -->

                                        <div class="maple__faq_accordion_item_header maple-trigger">

                                                                    <div class="maple__faq_accordion_item">
                                        <div class="maple__faq_accordion_item_header maple-trigger">
                                            Can I get a refund if I miss my bus due to unforeseen circumstances?                                        </div>
                                        <div class="maple__faq_accordion_item_body">
                                            <p><span style="font-weight: 400">Unfortunately, we cannot offer refunds for missed buses due to unforeseen circumstances, as the ticket guarantees a seat on a specific departure. However, we understand that unexpected situations can occur, and we recommend reaching out to our customer support team. They may be able to assist you with alternative options or rescheduling, subject to availability and our discretion.</span></p>                                        </div>
                                        <div class="maple-trigger maple__faq_accordion_item_icon">

                                                                    <div class="maple__faq_accordion_item">
                                        <div class="maple__faq_accordion_item_header maple-trigger">
                                            What happens if my bus is canceled or there is a significant delay? Will I receive a refund?                                        </div>

    function hideAll(elems) {
      for (var e = 0; e < elems.length; e++) {
        elems[e].style.display = 'none';
      }
    }
    window.onload = function() {
      hideAll(document.querySelectorAll('ol.pre-context'));

    function toggle() {
      for (var i = 0; i < arguments.length; i++) {
        var e = document.getElementById(arguments[i]);
        if (e) {
          e.style.display = e.style.display == 'none' ? 'block': 'none';
        }
      }
      return false;
    }
    function switchPastebinFriendly(link) {
      s1 = "Switch to copy-and-paste view";
      s2 = "Switch back to interactive view";
      link.textContent = link.textContent.trim() == s1 ? s2: s1;
      toggle('browserTraceback', 'pastebinTraceback');
      return false;

    function toggle() {

    <p>
      You‚Äôre seeing this error because you have <code>DEBUG = True</code> in your

    <script>
        // Dynamically generate the manifest location URL. It must be served from the document origin, and we may have
        // the base pointing to the CDN. This way we can generate a full URL which will bypass the base.
        document.querySelector('#manifest-placeholder').setAttribute('href', window.location.origin + '/manifest.json');

        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            if (!JitsiMeetJS.app) {
                return;
            }

            JitsiMeetJS.app.renderEntryPoint({
                Component: JitsiMeetJS.app.entryPoints.APP
            })

            const inIframe = () => {
                try {
                    return window.self !== window.top;
                } catch (e) {
                    return true;
                }
            };

            const isElectron = navigator.userAgent.includes('Electron');
            const shouldRegisterWorker = !isElectron && !inIframe() && 'serviceWorker' in navigator;

            if (shouldRegisterWorker) {
                navigator.serviceWorker
                    .register(window.location.origin + '/pwa-worker.js')
                    .then(reg => {
                        console.log('Service worker registered.', reg);
                    })
                    .catch(err => {
                        console.log(err);
                    });
            }
        });
    </script>
    <script>
        // IE11 and earlier can be identified via their user agent and be
        // redirected to a page that is known to have no newer js syntax.
        if (window.navigator.userAgent.match(/(MSIE|Trident)/)) {
            var roomName = encodeURIComponent(window.location.pathname);
            window.location.pathname = 'static/recommendedBrowsers.html';
        }

        window.indexLoadedTime = window.performance.now();
        console.log("(TIME) index.html loaded:\t", indexLoadedTime);
        // XXX the code below listeners for errors and displays an error message
        // in the document body when any of the required files fails to load.
        // The intention is to prevent from displaying broken page.
        var criticalFiles = [
            "config.js",
            "utils.js",
            "do_external_connect.js",
            "interface_config.js",
            "logging_config.js",
            "lib-jitsi-meet.min.js",
            "app.bundle.min.js",
            "all.css?v=6155"
        ];
        var loadErrHandler = function(e) {
            var target = e.target;
            // Error on <script> and <link>(CSS)
            // <script> will have .src and <link> .href
            var fileRef = (target.src ? target.src : target.href);
            if (("SCRIPT" === target.tagName || "LINK" === target.tagName)
                && criticalFiles.some(
                    function(file) { return fileRef.indexOf(file) !== -1 })) {
                window.onload = function() {
                    // The whole complex part below implements page reloads with
                    // "exponential backoff". The retry attempt is passes as
                    // "rCounter" query parameter
                    var href = window.location.href;

                    var retryMatch = href.match(/.+(\?|&)rCounter=(\d+)/);
                    var retryCountStr = retryMatch ? retryMatch[2] : "0";
                    var retryCount = Number.parseInt(retryCountStr);

                    if (retryMatch == null) {
                        var separator = href.indexOf("?") === -1 ? "?" : "&";
                        var hashIdx = href.indexOf("#");

                        if (hashIdx === -1) {
                            href += separator + "rCounter=1";
                        } else {
                            var hashPart = href.substr(hashIdx);

                            href = href.substr(0, hashIdx)
                                + separator + "rCounter=1" + hashPart;
                        }
                    } else {
                        var separator = retryMatch[1];

                        href = href.replace(
                            /(\?|&)rCounter=(\d+)/,
                            separator + "rCounter=" + (retryCount + 1));
                    }

                    var delay = Math.pow(2, retryCount) * 2000;
                    if (isNaN(delay) || delay < 2000 || delay > 60000)
                        delay = 10000;

                    var showMoreText = "show more";
                    var showLessText = "show less";

                    document.body.innerHTML
                        = "<div style='"
                        + "position: absolute;top: 50%;left: 50%;"
                        + "text-align: center;"
                        + "font-size: medium;"
                        + "font-weight: 400;"
                        + "transform: translate(-50%, -50%)'>"
                        + "Uh oh! We couldn't fully download everything we needed :("
                        + "<br/> "
                        + "We will try again shortly. In the mean time, check for problems with your Internet connection!"
                        + "<br/><br/> "
                        + "<div id='moreInfo' style='"
                        + "display: none;'>" + "Missing " + fileRef
                        + "<br/><br/></div>"
                        + "<a id='showMore' style='"
                        + "text-decoration: underline;"
                        + "font-size:small;"
                        + "cursor: pointer'>" + showMoreText + "</a>"
                        + "&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"
                        + "<a id ='reloadLink' style='"
                        + "text-decoration: underline;"
                        + "font-size:small;"
                        + "'>reload now</a>"
                        + "</div>";

                    var reloadLink = document.getElementById('reloadLink');
                    reloadLink.setAttribute('href', href);

                    var showMoreElem = document.getElementById("showMore");
                    showMoreElem.addEventListener('click', function () {
                            var moreInfoElem
                                    = document.getElementById("moreInfo");

                            if (showMoreElem.innerHTML === showMoreText) {
                                moreInfoElem.setAttribute(
                                    "style",
                                    "display: block;"
                                    + "color:#FF991F;"
                                    + "font-size:small;"
                                    + "user-select:text;");
                                showMoreElem.innerHTML = showLessText;
                            }
                            else {
                                moreInfoElem.setAttribute(
                                    "style", "display: none;");
                                showMoreElem.innerHTML = showMoreText;
                            }
                        });

                    window.setTimeout(
                        function () { window.location.replace(href); }, delay);

                    // Call extra handler if defined.
                    if (typeof postLoadErrorHandler === "function") {
                        postLoadErrorHandler(fileRef);
                    }
                };
                window.removeEventListener(
                    'error', loadErrHandler, true /* capture phase */);
            }
        };
        window.addEventListener(
            'error', loadErrHandler, true /* capture phase type of listener */);
    </script>

var config = {
    // Connection
    //

    hosts: {
        // XMPP domain.
        domain: 'meet.crustybuns.ca',

        // When using authentication, domain for guest users.
        anonymousdomain: 'guest.meet.crustybuns.ca',

        // Domain for authenticated users. Defaults to <domain>.
